snippet.textDisplay:
40lbs is 18kgs. This man basically carried a bag of dog food to the ring. Except, that weight was well distributed on his neck shoulders and torso.

I dunno about you, but when I’m carrying a bag of dog food on my shoulder, it’s my shoulders that hurt first, not my legs.

A better excuse would have been that for a solid hour before the fight he was pacing backwards and forwards and shadow boxing using all of his energy.

He needs to stop making awful excuses. The sooner he accepts that he was outboxed and out punched by the heavier man, the quicker he can move on and try and figure out how to beat him in the third fight.

My advice to him would be, you look terrible going backwards, you need to learn to move better and counter in a defensive position.

You need to work on slipping that right.

Every time Tyson has been on the floor he’s got back up, so relying on your punching power isn’t enough.

You have to try and box your way through it. When he throws, you throw.

Learn to throw your big shots at a short distance, it’s no good relying on that space when the man in front of you won’t give it too you.

Work on the body, empty his gas tank early and he’s more susceptible to bigger shots later on.

At this stage in your career it’s impossible to outbox Tyson. So you have to make it a war.
